<subSubSection id="B3F465128F353E41FA0BFF14F811FB08" pageId="7" pageNumber="379" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="FB5136998F353E41FA0BFF14F811FB08" blockId="7.[1472,2679,731,1269]" pageId="7" pageNumber="379">
<emphasis id="C99AEA8B8F353E41FA0BFF14F889FB92" bold="true" box="[1474,1827,1078,1111]" pageId="7" pageNumber="379">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List (as 
<taxonomicName id="3CEE4D1A8F353E41F5E0FF14F9DDFBBB" baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1899" class="Mammalia" family="Erethizontidae" genus="Sphiggurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="7" pageNumber="379" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vestitus">Sphiggurus vestitus</taxonomicName>
). The Blackish Hairy Dwarf Porcupine is extremely rare and known from only a few individual specimens. The region where specimens were originally collected has been almost entirely deforested.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
